<i>noun</i>: 플루토늄 <br>
<ul>
<li>
<i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>플루토늄</dt><br>
<dd>a solid silvery grey radioactive transuranic element whose atoms can be split when bombarded with neutrons; found in minute quantities in uranium ores but is usually synthesized in nuclear reactors; 13 isotopes are known with the most important being plutonium 239</dd><br>
<dd><i>synonyms</i>: plutonium, Pu, atomic number 94</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>
